The Study of the Drilling Core Features of a Multi-pipe Deep Lunar  
Soil Sampling Driller for Manned Lunar Exploration based on the  
Discrete Element Technology*  
Kailiang Zhang, Xuyan Hou*, Wanjing Pan, Tianxiang Ding and Zongquan Deng  

lunar soil sampling is to make sure the enough output power,  
drilling pressure and the reliability of the driller.  
Abstract—Lunar soil sampling is important for human beings  
to know about the components of lunar soil and the lunar  
geological structure. By now, lunar soil between the depths 0 and  
3 meters is researched, but there are not any drillers which can  
collect the much deeper lunar soil. In this paper, a multi-pipe  
driller that can drill 5 meters deep for manned lunar exploration  
was proposed. In order to verify the reliability of drilling core,  
the drilling core features of the driller were studied by using the  
EDEM software. The influences of drill pipes rotation speed and  
feed rate to the drilling core were studied. The results turned out  
that the feed rate had a significant influence on the drilling core  
features and the rotation speed had an important influence on  
the power and the torque. The simulation results can provide  
guidance for the optimization of the system structure and the  
technical supports to China’s deep lunar soil sampling project.  
With the development of China's space technology and  
lunar exploration project, the next plan of lunar exploration is  
that landing the astronauts on the moon. At that time our  
country will launch an explorer which can provide a high load  
working platform and enough output power. Besides, the  
astronauts will take part in the activity of deep lunar soil  
sampling. He or she will help the driller accomplish the  
collection of lunar soil. This can increase the reliability of the  
driller. And the project of deep lunar soil sampling can carry  
out smoothly.  
The realization of the goal of deep lunar soil sampling  
needs the interconnection of drill pipes because of the  
restriction of the size of the explorer. Many countries have  
carried out the study that samples were collected by multi-pipe  
drillers. And some research results are shown in Figure 1 [2-5].  
I. INTRODUCTION  
Lunar soil sampling is one of the most important methods  
for human beings to know about the components of lunar soil  
and the geological structures of the moon, and it has a  
significant value for people to utilize the resources of the moon.  
It is also a good place to establish bases and study the evolution  
mechanism of the universe. However, nowadays people only  
know about the lunar soil between the depths 0 and 3 meters. It  
is far from the aims that people know about the components of  
lunar soil absolutely. So it will be a long and hard task to  
collect the deeper lunar soil.  
It is an important method to get the deep lunar soil samples  
by using the driller. However, the density and cohesion of the  
soil increases with the increase of drilling depth, the result is  
that power and drilling force of driller increases with the  
drilling depth gradually. In American Apollo programs, the  
astronauts collected the samples by carrying the driller and  
providing the drilling pressure by his own gravity, the max  
drilling depth was 3meters[1]. The Former Soviet’s probes of  
Luna series used unmanned and automated sampling drillers to  
achieve the drilling depth of 2.5 m [1]. So the deeper lunar soil  
sampling will put forward a higher requirement about the  
output power and the load of the working platform of the  
explorer. Besides, the hard environment of the moon will also  
influence the reliability of the driller. So the fundament of deep

B. the mechanical properties of lunar soil  
The compression of lunar soil: the feature that the volume  
of lunar soil reduces under the pressure is called the  
compression of lunar soil. Experimental research shows  
that under ordinary pressure, the compression of soil  
particles is much smaller than the total amount of  
compression, so the compression of soil particles can be  
neglected completely. That’s to say, the compression of  
lunar soil is considered to be the shrink of the lunar soil  
void volume [11-13].  
II. THE CHARACTERS OF LUNAR SOIL  
Lunar soil is mixture of broken rock debris, powder and  
breccia formed by meteorite impacts, cosmic ray  
bombardment, high and low temperature alternating in the  
condition without oxygen, water, wind and life. Because of  
the influence of the special environment of the moon,  
compared with earth's soil, the lunar soil shows some unique  
physical and mechanical properties [6-7].  
The compression of lunar soil is determined by the  
coefficient of compressibility, compression exponent,  
modulus of compression, modulus of deformation and  
stress history. Under the condition of static pressure, the  
compression factors of soil whose void ratio is different are  
shown in TABLE III.  
A. The Physical Properties of Lunar Soil  
The shape of lunar soil particles: The particle morphology  
of lunar soil is quite complicated. It changes from sphere to  
angular shape. Long strip shaped particles, sub-angular  
particles and angular particles are more common. The  
morphology diagram of lunar soil in scanning electron  
microscope is shown in Figure 2[8].

The shear resistance of lunar soil ：Lunar soil is discrete,  
and the bonding force between soil particles is far less than the  
particles’ strength. Under the effect of external force, the  
relative sliding between the part of soil particles and another  
part of soil particles will happen. The resistance performance  
of sliding of different soil particles is different, and the  
resistance performance of sliding is called the shear strength  
of lunar soil. The shear strength of lunar soil can be expressed  
by the following equation [14].

The size distribution of lunar soil particles: The size  
distribution of lunar soil particles is wide. Diameters of most  
lunar soil particles are between 30μm and 1mm. The  
separation of lunar soil is poor. Its median diameter is from  
40μm t 130μm and the average number is 70μm, which is  
similar to silt [9].

III. THE MULTI-PIPE DRILLER AND THE ANALYSIS OF THE  
FACTORS INFLUENCING THE DRILLING CORE FEATURES  
A. The Model of the Multi-Pipe Driller  
In order to collect deeper lunar soil, a new driller that can  
collect the lunar soil between the depths 0 and 5 meters was  
proposed. It realized the goals of deep lunar soil sampling by  
the interconnection of drill pipes and the coinstantaneous  
contra-rotation of the inside drill pipes and the outside drill  
pipes (the detailed principle of drilling core will be described  
in the drilling core mechanism). The driller is consist of a  
lunar soil drilling mechanism, a mechanism recovering  
samples , a mechanism fixing drill pipes, a mechanism  
interchanging drill pipes and some drill tools. The structure of  
the driller is shown in Figure 4.  
a) The drill pipes of drilling core  
b) The upper part of drilling core

B. The work flow of the multi-pipe driller  
The entire sampling system is consists of many modules,  
the task of lunar soil sampling is accomplished by the orderly  
work of each module. The Figure 6 shows the working  
process of the first group drill pipes.  
12——groups of drill pipes  
2343  
Authorized licensed use limited to: JILIN UNIVERSITY. Downloaded on January 03,2025 at 01:42:46 UTC from IEEE Xplore. Restrictions apply.  
If the soil in the upper positon of drilling core mechanism  
has good drilling core features, the soil between the inside  
drill pipes and the outside drill pipes won’t accumulate either.  
So this paper mainly analyzed the drilling core features of soil  
in the upper positon of coring mechanism. The factors that  
influence the core features of soil are as follows.  
The RPM of inside drill pipes: When the RPM of outside  
drill pipes and the feed rate are constant, with the  
improvement of the RPM of inside drill pipes, the convey  
amount of soil in unit time increases gradually at first, and  
then the growth trend becomes slow. If the amount of soil  
arriving in the upper parts of drilling core mechanism is more  
than the amount of soil departing from the drilling core  
mechanism in unit time, the lunar soil will accumulate in this  
position, and the drill pipes may be stuck by the accumulated  
soil.  
a) Initial state b) Clamping part moves up c) Interchanging part rotates  
The feed rate of drill pipes: When the rotation speed of  
inside drill pipes and outside drill pipes are constant, the  
filling rate of soil in the spiral grooves is proportional to the  
feed rate of drill pipes [16]. The filling rate of lunar soil will  
be higher when the feed rate of drill pipes is higher. Thus the  
drill pipes are easy to be stuck by the soil.  
c) Interconnection of drill d) Driving joints moves up e) Interchanging part  
restors  
IV. THE SIMULATION BASED ON THE EDEM  
A. The simulation model of the upper parts of the drilling  
core mechanism  
Under the condition that the simulation results were not  
affected, in order to speed up the simulation process, the  
geometry has been equivalent simplified. On the one hand, the  
screws, bearings, bearing caps and other parts were removed,  
leaving only the inside driving joint, the outside driving joint  
and samples guiding part. On the other hand, an equivalent  
Plane was added at the bottom of the upper parts of coring  
mechanism to simulate the function between the soil in drill  
pipes and soil in the upper parts of coring mechanism. The  
simplified model is shown in Figure 7.  
f) Drill pipes drill  
g) Separation of drill  
h) Driving joints moves up  
Figure 6. The working process of first group drill pipes  
When the work of first drill group completes, the driving  
joints reset, then the next drill group begins to work. And the  
goal driving 5 meters deep will come true after the  
interconnection of all drill pipes.  
C. The analysis of the factors that influence the drilling  
core features.  
The friction between the inner wall of outside drill pipes  
and the lunar soil in the spiral grooves of inside drill pipes is  
the main impetus pushing the lunar soil move up. There is  
only a 1 mm gap between the inside drill pipes and outside  
drill pipes. So it is easy to happen that the drill pipes are stuck  
by the soil.  
a) the upper parts of coring mechanism b) the wireframe in EDEM  
1—— the inside driving joint  
2——samples guiding part  
3——the outside driving joint  
As we know, the drilling core mechanism is consists of  
drilling tools and upper parts of drilling core. About the  
drilling tools, the spirals of inside drill pipes can transport the  
lunar soil to the upper position of the drilling core mechanism  
as long as the RPM of inside drill pipes is appropriate. It’s not  
easy to happen that lunar soil accumulates between the inside  
drill pipes and the outside drill pipes. But the soil in the upper  
drilling core mechanism needs to rely on its own motion to go  
through the part guiding the soil turn into the mechanism  
recovering the samples, and the liquidity of lunar soil is poor  
because of the large angle of internal friction. So the soil is  
easy to accumulate in the upper part of drilling core.  
4——equivalent Planar of the below soil

B. The simulation model of lunar soil  
The shapes of lunar soil particles are mostly elongated and  
prismatic. In EDEM simulation, based on the equivalent  
method of rolling [17-18], the corresponding rolling friction  
coefficient of non-spherical particles and spherical particles  
was determined by comparing the angle of repose α (shown in  
Figure 8). Then the rolling friction coefficient of spherical  
particles of simulated lunar soil was increased, and the

The conclusion got from the simulation results was as  
follows.  
(1) When the feed rate is constant(Particles generation  
rate is 10000/s), if the RPM of inside drill pipes is increased,  
the variation trend of the filling rate of lunar soil in the upper  
position of drilling core mechanism is unsharp, and the value  
of filling rate is small. So the lunar soil won’t accumulate in  
this position and causes the jam of driller.  
(2) The average axial velocity of soil, the power of system  
and the torque all increased with the increase of the RPM of  
inside drill pipes. There is a need to select the appropriate  
RPM for the purpose that the lunar soil has high transmission  
speed but the power and torque are not too big.  
The influence of the feed rate on the core features of soil：  
We have known that when the rotation speed of inside drill  
pipes and outside drill pipes are constant, the filling rate of

soil, two comparative tests that the particle generation rate

V. CONCLUSION  
This paper presented a new type of lunar soil sampler  
which can drill 5 meters deep. Besides, the drilling core  
features of the driller were studied by using the EDEM  
software. The influence trend of drill pipes rotation speed and  
feed rate to the drilling core was got according to the  
simulation results.  
The structure of the drilling core mechanism will be  
optimized according to the simulation results. Then the  
processing prototype will be produced to carry out the  
experiments.
